narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: - the course material is repetitive- moderate workload- interesting topic if you haven't learned about it before- many undergraduates
Difficult for PhD students. Reading requirements difficult when carrying full term load added to this is the cost of buying books, which are now non-returnable.
One of the best courses at Yale - highly recommended for undergraduate and graduate students.

This class covers health disparities by focusing on the confluence of gender, race/ethnicity, and social class. It is a great choice for anyone studying health, especially women's health, but should only be taken by those who enjoy reading and discussion.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Broadened my understanding of women's health issues globally and nationally.
